description: Octopus octopodia (the common octopus) + -ine (chemically basic or alkaloidal substance)

entries.meaning: (chemistry) An analog of lactic acid, derived from the amino acids arginine and alanine, first isolated from the muscle tissue of octopus species.

adjectives.description: octopine (comparative more octopine, superlative most octopine)

entries.meaning: Of, pertaining to, or resembling an octopus or octopuses; octopuslike.
